TITLE: Merging Maps with map.merge() in Sass
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use map.merge() to combine two maps, with the second map's values taking precedence for duplicate keys.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sass/sass-site/blob/main/source/documentation/modules/map.md#2025-04-09_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: scss
CODE:
```
@use "sass:map";

$light-weights: ("lightest": 100, "light": 300);
$heavy-weights: ("medium": 500, "bold": 700);

@debug map.merge($light-weights, $heavy-weights);
// ("lightest": 100, "light": 300, "medium": 500, "bold": 700)
```

LANGUAGE: sass
CODE:
```
@use "sass:map"

$light-weights: ("lightest": 100, "light": 300)
$heavy-weights: ("medium": 500, "bold": 700)

@debug map.merge($light-weights, $heavy-weights)
// ("lightest": 100, "light": 300, "medium": 500, "bold": 700)
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Variable Scope in Sass
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates variable scope in Sass. Global variables are accessible throughout the stylesheet after declaration, while local variables are only accessible within the block they're declared in.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sass/sass-site/blob/main/source/documentation/variables.md#2025-04-09_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: scss
CODE:
```
$global-variable: global value;

.content {
  $local-variable: local value;
  global: $global-variable;
  local: $local-variable;
}

.sidebar {
  global: $global-variable;

  // This would fail, because $local-variable isn't in scope:
  // local: $local-variable;
}
```

LANGUAGE: sass
CODE:
```
$global-variable: global value

.content
  $local-variable: local value
  global: $global-variable
  local: $local-variable


.sidebar
  global: $global-variable

  // This would fail, because $local-variable isn't in scope:
  // local: $local-variable
```

