TITLE: Implementing a Higher-Order Function in Sass
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to create a higher-order function in Sass that takes a list of numbers and a function as arguments. It applies the given function to each number in the list and returns the results.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sass/sass-site/blob/main/source/documentation/values/functions.md#2025-04-09_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: scss
CODE:
```
@use 'sass:list';
@use 'sass:meta';

@function transform($list, $function) {
  $result: ();
  @each $item in $list {
    $result: list.append($result, meta.call($function, $item));
  }
  @return $result;
}

@function double($number) {
  @return $number * 2;
}

.powers {
  of-two: transform((1, 2, 3, 4), meta.get-function("double"));
}
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Sass Mixin with Optional Arguments
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to create a mixin with optional arguments that have default values. This example creates a text replacement mixin with customizable background positioning.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sass/sass-site/blob/main/source/documentation/at-rules/mixin.md#2025-04-09_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: scss
CODE:
```
@mixin replace-text($image, $x: 50%, $y: 50%) {
  text-indent: -99999em;
  overflow: hidden;
  text-align: left;

  background: {
    image: $image;
    repeat: no-repeat;
    position: $x $y;
  }
}

.mail-icon {
  @include replace-text(url("/images/mail.svg"), 0);
}
```

LANGUAGE: sass
CODE:
```
@mixin replace-text($image, $x: 50%, $y: 50%)
  text-indent: -99999em
  overflow: hidden
  text-align: left

  background:
    image: $image
    repeat: no-repeat
    position: $x $y

.mail-icon
  @include replace-text(url("/images/mail.svg"), 0)
```

