TITLE: Defining a Fibonacci Function in Sass
DESCRIPTION: Creates a function that calculates the Fibonacci number at position n, then uses it to set a sidebar margin. The function builds the Fibonacci sequence using a loop and returns the nth value.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sass/sass-site/blob/main/source/documentation/at-rules/function.md#2025-04-09_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: scss
CODE:
```
@function fibonacci($n) {
  $sequence: 0 1;
  @for $_ from 1 through $n {
    $new: nth($sequence, length($sequence)) + nth($sequence, length($sequence) - 1);
    $sequence: append($sequence, $new);
  }
  @return nth($sequence, length($sequence));
}

.sidebar {
  float: left;
  margin-left: fibonacci(4) * 1px;
}
```

LANGUAGE: sass
CODE:
```
@function fibonacci($n)
  $sequence: 0 1
  @for $_ from 1 through $n
    $new: nth($sequence, length($sequence)) + nth($sequence, length($sequence) - 1)
    $sequence: append($sequence, $new)
  @return nth($sequence, length($sequence))

.sidebar
  float: left
  margin-left: fibonacci(4) * 1px
```

