TITLE: Adjusting Color Channels in SCSS
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates using color.adjust() to modify color channels by fixed amounts. Shows adjustments in different color spaces including RGB, LAB, and OKLCH.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sass/sass-site/blob/main/source/documentation/modules/color.md#2025-04-09_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: scss
CODE:
```
@use 'sass:color';

@debug color.adjust(#6b717f, $red: 15); // #7a717f
@debug color.adjust(lab(40% 30 40), $lightness: 10%, $a: -20); // lab(50% 10 40)
@debug color.adjust(#d2e1dd, $hue: 45deg, $space: oklch);
// rgb(209.7987626149, 223.8632000471, 229.3988769575)
```

