TITLE: Using @for Loop with Variable Interpolation in Sass
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates using a @for loop to create different background colors for list elements. It iterates from 1 through 3, using the loop variable to both select elements with nth-child and calculate progressively lighter background colors using the lighten function.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sass/sass-site/blob/main/source/documentation/at-rules/control/for.md#2025-04-09_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: scss
CODE:
```
$base-color: #036;

@for $i from 1 through 3 {
  ul:nth-child(3n + #{$i}) {
    background-color: lighten($base-color, $i * 5%);
  }
}
```

LANGUAGE: sass
CODE:
```
$base-color: #036

@for $i from 1 through 3
  ul:nth-child(3n + #{$i})
    background-color: lighten($base-color, $i * 5%)
```

