TITLE: Using Placeholder Selectors with @extend in Sass
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create and extend placeholder selectors in Sass. The example shows a %toolbelt placeholder that defines common styles which are then extended by .action-buttons and .reset-buttons classes. The placeholder selector itself won't appear in the final CSS output.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sass/sass-site/blob/main/source/documentation/style-rules/placeholder-selectors.md#2025-04-09_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: scss
CODE:
```
%toolbelt {
  box-sizing: border-box;
  border-top: 1px rgba(#000, .12) solid;
  padding: 16px 0;
  width: 100%;

  &:hover { border: 2px rgba(#000, .5) solid; }
}

.action-buttons {
  @extend %toolbelt;
  color: #4285f4;
}

.reset-buttons {
  @extend %toolbelt;
  color: #cddc39;
}
```

LANGUAGE: sass
CODE:
```
%toolbelt
  box-sizing: border-box
  border-top: 1px rgba(#000, .12) solid
  padding: 16px 0
  width: 100%

  &:hover
    border: 2px rgba(#000, .5) solid

.action-buttons
  @extend %toolbelt
  color: #4285f4


.reset-buttons
  @extend %toolbelt
  color: #cddc39
```

