TITLE: Using Argument Lists with Keyword Handling in Sass Mixins
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to handle arbitrary arguments in mixins, including capturing and processing keyword arguments. This example creates a flexible border mixin that works with multiple syntaxes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sass/sass-site/blob/main/source/documentation/values/lists.md#2025-04-09_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: scss
CODE:
```
@use "sass:meta";

@mixin border($width, $args...) {
  border-width: $width;

  // Extract keyword arguments like $color and $style
  $kwargs: meta.keywords($args);

  @if map-has-key($kwargs, color) {
    border-color: map-get($kwargs, color);
  }

  @if map-has-key($kwargs, style) {
    border-style: map-get($kwargs, style);
  }
}
```

LANGUAGE: sass
CODE:
```
@use "sass:meta"

@mixin border($width, $args...)
  border-width: $width

  // Extract keyword arguments like $color and $style
  $kwargs: meta.keywords($args)

  @if map-has-key($kwargs, color)
    border-color: map-get($kwargs, color)

  @if map-has-key($kwargs, style)
    border-style: map-get($kwargs, style)
```

