TITLE: Creating a scale-below function with @while loops in Sass
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates a function that uses a @while loop to repeatedly divide a value by a ratio until it falls below a base value. The example shows both the function definition and its practical application for scaling font sizes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sass/sass-site/blob/main/source/documentation/at-rules/control/while.md#2025-04-09_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: scss
CODE:
```
@use "sass:math";

/// Divides `$value` by `$ratio` until it's below `$base`.
@function scale-below($value, $base, $ratio: 1.618) {
  @while $value > $base {
    $value: math.div($value, $ratio);
  }
  @return $value;
}

$normal-font-size: 16px;
sup {
  font-size: scale-below(20px, 16px);
}
```

