TITLE: HTML Ancestor Handling in Sass @extend
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how Sass handles complex selector ancestors when using @extend, showing that not all possible combinations are generated to maintain stylesheet efficiency.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sass/sass-site/blob/main/source/documentation/at-rules/extend.md#2025-04-09_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: scss
CODE:
```
header .warning li {
  font-weight: bold;
}

aside .notice dd {
  // Sass doesn't generate CSS to match the <dd> in
  //
  // <header>
  //   <aside>
  //     <div class="warning">
  //       <div class="notice">
  //         <dd>...</dd>
  //       </div>
  //     </div>
  //   </aside>
  // </header>
  //
  // because matching all elements like that would require us to generate nine
  // new selectors instead of just two.
  @extend li;
}
```

LANGUAGE: sass
CODE:
```
