TITLE: Using @return with Early Returns in Sass
DESCRIPTION: Implements a string insertion function with early return optimization. The function checks if the input string is empty and returns immediately if so, otherwise processes the string by slicing it at the specified index and inserting new content.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sass/sass-site/blob/main/source/documentation/at-rules/function.md#2025-04-09_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: scss
CODE:
```
@use "sass:string";

@function str-insert($string, $insert, $index) {
  // Avoid making new strings if we don't need to.
  @if string.length($string) == 0 {
    @return $insert;
  }

  $before: string.slice($string, 0, $index);
  $after: string.slice($string, $index);
  @return $before + $insert + $after;
}
```

LANGUAGE: sass
CODE:
```
@use "sass:string"

@function str-insert($string, $insert, $index)
  // Avoid making new strings if we don't need to.
  @if string.length($string) == 0
    @return $insert


  $before: string.slice($string, 0, $index)
  $after: string.slice($string, $index)
  @return $before + $insert + $after
```

