TITLE: Using First-Class Mixin Values with meta.get-mixin() and meta.apply() in Sass
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to work with mixin values in Sass. It shows how to define a mixin, retrieve it as a value using meta.get-mixin(), and then dynamically apply it using meta.apply(). This technique enables creating extensible components with customizable styles.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sass/sass-site/blob/main/source/documentation/values/mixins.md#2025-04-09_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: scss
CODE:
```
@use "sass:meta";

/// Applies styles to make an element appear like a button.
@mixin button($background: #6b717f) {
  display: inline-block;
  border-radius: 4px;
  padding: 0.5em 1em;
  background: $background;
  color: white;
  font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;
  font-size: 1em;
}

@mixin primary-button {
  // Get the `button` mixin and store it in a variable.
  $button: meta.get-mixin(button);

  // Call the `button` mixin with hot pink as the background.
  @include meta.apply($button, #e91e63);

  font-weight: bold;
  text-transform: uppercase;
}

.my-button {
  @include primary-button;
}
```

