TITLE: Using min() and max() Functions in Sass
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how min() and max() functions are parsed differently based on their content. Shows both CSS calculation cases and SassScript function calls using modulo operator.
SOURCE: https://github.com/sass/sass-site/blob/main/source/documentation/values/calculations.md#2025-04-09_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: scss
CODE:
```
$padding: 12px;

.post {
  padding-left: max($padding, env(safe-area-inset-left));
  padding-right: max($padding, env(safe-area-inset-right));
}

.sidebar {
  padding-left: max($padding % 10, 20px);
  padding-right: max($padding % 10, 20px);
}
```

